The paper discusses multiband spectrum access in cognitive radio networks, which involves sensing and accessing multiple bands to improve network throughput and spectrum maintenance. This topic falls under the category of networked and internet-based systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses signal processing techniques such as wavelet-based methods and compressive sensing, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper addresses challenges and limitations in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic in computer networks and communications (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SI).
